div1.p:
I am fifteen, the 17th of last December; (I am son to
George Lomas
) somebody knocked at our door, on Monday, the 17th of December; the maid-servant went down and would not open it; then I went down, and I knew Mr. Wainwright, the patrol, and he brought the prisoner with him, and he asked, whether he belonged to the house; I never saw the prisoner before.
